summary: Well-endowed in taking on leadership positions, both inside my area of specialties and outside. Highly adaptive to changing environments of both work and pace. Over 4 years of educational leadership and customer service. Skilled in communication, collaboration, and independent work. Goal-oriented with excellent customer service, organizational and time management abilities. Able to connect with diverse populations and resolve conflicts. Proficient in Microsoft Word, Excel, and PowerPoint.

experience.title: Office Staff
experience.description: Duties included managing multi-line customer service phones, stage setup, routine office tasks, assisting with school events, coordinating and hosting new student orientations, visiting high schools to recruit new students for CGCC, interviewing students about their college experience, and participating in TV commercials to represent the college.

experience.title: Public Relations Officer/ Vice-President
experience.description: Led efforts to involve more students in campus events, guided scholars toward success, maintained a high GPA, donated time to charity events and community/college services, and represented the group in campus activities.

experience.title: Student Leader
experience.description: Led the Light Feet project at the Pecos/Williams Field Campus, organized fundraisers and shoe drives with a goal of collecting 100 pairs of shoes, socks, and laces for Malawi, Africa.

experience.title: Volunteer Patient Care (Interventional Cardiology and NICU)
experience.description: Volunteered in NICU and interventional cardiology; assisted with patient intake, scheduling, and supportive care; helped nurses and doctors with patient needs.

experience.title: Volunteer
experience.description: Volunteer for Camp Kesem to support children affected by cancer; engage with families and provide joy and relief to participants.
